                                    <watches>4</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15307103" author="maropu" created="Tue, 31 May 2016 02:24:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I couldn&apos;t find the best solution for this issue though, it seems at least we&apos;d better to limit #parallelism for this file listing before the v2.0 release&lt;br/&gt;
because users might get surprised at generating many tasks in case of large defaultParallellism.&lt;br/&gt;
I know we can control this by defaultParallelism though, this seems to be not suitable for that because it is a global option.&lt;br/&gt;
One of solutions is to set (paths.size / parallelPartitionDiscoveryThreshold + 1) at the number.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/compare/master...maropu:SPARK-15530&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/compare/master...maropu:SPARK-15530&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thought?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15309240" author="yhuai" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2016 04:32:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Your change looks reasonable. How about we just take the value of sparkSession.sessionState.conf.parallelPartitionDiscoveryThreshold? We can change the doc of this conf and increate the default value. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15309246" author="maropu" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2016 04:42:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You suggest we should rename the value and change the default value?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15309250" author="yhuai" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2016 04:46:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The doc of that conf says &quot;The degree of parallelism for schema merging and partition discovery of Parquet data sources.&quot;. So seems it just means parallelism. I am not sure why the variable name has a &quot;threshold&quot; at the end. It will be great if you can check when we added that conf. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right now, I am inclined to use that conf to configure the parallelism (we need to make that conf an internal conf though). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15309261" author="maropu" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2016 04:55:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, I see. Okay, then I&apos;ll check the logs  and make pr later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15310541" author="apachespark" created="Wed, 1 Jun 2016 16:06:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;maropu&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13444&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13444&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
